# Scouting fixtures are intentionally tracked (they are the contract for the
# next change). The exception below overrides the *.parquet rule above.
!scouting/**/*.parquet
# HumanEval Direct Completion's canonical RunRecord parquet is the only
# path-of-record for the controlled run (provider non-determinism means it
# cannot be regenerated byte-identically from a re-run). Track it. Other
# example/* parquets stay gitignored — they are regenerated from `make_runs.py`
# at test time.
!examples/humaneval-direct-completion/runs.parquet
# SWE-bench Verified OpenHands public-submission audit: the canonical run
# parquet is regenerated by `tools/regenerate_swe_bench_verified.py` from
# public artifacts (HF dataset + swe-bench/experiments results.json), but
# we track it so the snapshot test, CLI default path, and `make check` work
# offline without re-fetching ~ 12 KB of frozen public data.
!examples/swe-bench-verified-openhands/runs.parquet
# Terminal-Bench 2.0 Mux public-submission audit: track the canonical
# RunRecord parquet generated from the public HF leaderboard dataset so reports
# and tests work offline after regeneration.
!examples/terminal-bench-2-mux/runs.parquet

# Local scouting download cache: encrypted zips and decrypted JSON traces.
# Regenerable from huggingface.co/datasets/agent-evals/hal_traces.
.scout-cache/

# HumanEval Direct Completion raw + graded API responses.
# Regeneratable from the API and grader.
scouting/humaneval-direct-completion/raw/
scouting/humaneval-direct-completion/graded/
